                <DIV class="ReviewHeading">Book Description:</DIV>
                <span id="Label1">This book covers middle-tier programming with PHP.<BR> PHP is a server-side, HTML-embedded scripting language. It is an open source technology, rapidly gaining popularity as a scripting language for people running dynamic websites. One of its major attractions over Perl, JavaScript and other scripting languages is that PHP has a built-in database integration layer and seamless IP connectivity, with LDAP and TCP as well as the IMAP mail interface. Features;<BR> Real world, practical experience and techniques<BR> From installation and configuration of the PHP engine to advanced dynamic application design<BR> Definitive coverage of core PHP language and database addressing:<BR> MySQL is covered in depth. <BR> Practical e-commerce and business scripting including database application development, together with PHP and XML applications.<BR> LDAP connectivity addressed.<BR></span>
              
</td></tr></table>
              <table id="CustomerReviewsPanel" class="ReviewSection" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0" width="100%"><tr><td>
	
                <DIV class="ReviewHeading">Customer reviews:</DIV>
                
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">For the last time, this is a must-have!</div>
                    <div>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Rating: </span>
                      <span>5</span>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Helpful: </span>
                      <span>0</span>
